The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The state government is planning action against TV shows featuring astrology, law minister Nisith Adhikary said on Friday. He, however, refused to divulge whether the government would enact a law to ban such programmes. Trinamul Congress MLA Sonali Guha had on Thursday raised the issue in the Assembly, observing that astrologers were doing roaring business by hiring slots on TV channels. Several people are being conned by the astrologers, she alleged. 

 hief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee agreed with Guha and announced that the law department would examine whether the channels beaming astrology shows could be prosecuted. 

 he government is also considering measures to prevent channels from telecasting criminal cases that are being probed or are sub-judice, Adhikary hinted.

 An armed gang looted an old-age home in Bishnupur, on the southern fringes of the city, on Friday afternoon. The criminals escaped with cash and jewellery worth more than Rs 1 lakh. They also assaulted a number of local residents. No one has been arrested. 

 Train services in the Sealdah (South) section were disrupted for about half an hour on Friday, following a crack in the tracks near Bondel Gate. Six trains were cancelled between 11.37 am and 12.14 pm, an official said. 

 Two persons were injured when an autorickshaw overturned on Bidhannagar Road around 10.40 am on Friday. Bishnu Roy Prasad, 45, and Paramanand Singh, 45, were admitted to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where their condition was stated to be critical. Both are residents of Katadanga, North 24-Parganas. The autorickshaw driver was not injured.

 Students of Calcutta University?s department of postgraduate diploma in media studies organised a seminar, New Indian Cinema: Perspective Reviewed, on Friday. 

 Rita Seal, 47, was injured after being knocked down by a Matador at the BT Road-Raja Manindra Road crossing on Friday afternoon. She was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital and later shifted to NRS Medical College and Hospital. Seal is a resident of Shimlai Para Lane, off BT Road. 

